Step 5. NOT (~)
NOT flips every bit.

0 →1
1 →0

Example
______________
|             |
| 5 00000101
|
| ~ 11111010
|______________|

Because computers use two's complement for signed integers, `~5` becomes `-6`.
We'll cover two's complement later.

