4. Check if kth bit is set
Suppose

n= 13
   1101


 Want to know if bit 2 is 1.    <<Create mask>>

1<<2 0100
________
|       |
| 1101
| 0100
| ----
| 0100
|_______|

Not zero.  Therefore bit 2 is ON.
Code
_____________________________
|                           |
| if ((n & (1 << k)) != 0)
|___________________________|

// Check if kth bit is set

console.log((13 &(1<<0)),(13 &(1<<0)) !=0)
//            1101        1101  0001
//         &  0001        true
//           ------
//            0001     that is 1

console.log((13 &(1<<1)),(13 &(1<<1)) !=0)
//            1101        1101  0010
//         &  0010        false
//           ------
//            0000      that is 0

console.log((13 &(1<<2)),(13 &(1<<2)) !=0)
//            1101        1101  0100
//         &  0100        true
//           ------
//            0100      that is 4

console.log((13 &(1<<3)),(13 &(1<<3)) !=0)
//            1101        1101  1000
//         &  1000        true
//           ------
//            1000       that is 8


5. Turn ON a bit

1001  Want  1101
________________
|              |
| n | (1 << k)
|______________|

// Turn ON kth bit

console.log((13 | (1<<0)))
//            1101
//         |  0001
//           ------
//            1101      that is 13 (already ON)

console.log((13 | (1<<1)))
//            1101
//         |  0010
//           ------
//            1111      that is 15

console.log((13 | (1<<2)))
//            1101
//         |  0100
//           ------
//            1101      that is 13 (already ON)

console.log((13 | (1<<3)))
//            1101
//         |  1000
//           ------
//            1101      that is 13 (already ON)

6. Turn OFF a bit

1101
↓
1001     Use
_________________
|               |
| n & ~(1 << k)
|_______________|
or n ^ (1<<k )
// Turn OFF kth bit

console.log((13 & ~(1<<0)))
//             1101
//         &   1110   (~0001)
//            ------
//             1100      that is 12

console.log((13 & ~(1<<1)))
//             1101
//         &   1101   (~0010)
//            ------
//             1101      that is 13 (already OFF)

console.log((13 & ~(1<<2)))
//             1101
//         &   1011   (~0100)
//            ------
//             1001      that is 9

console.log((13 & ~(1<<3)))
//             1101
//         &   0111   (~1000)
//            ------
//             0101      that is 5


